{"id":13192,"date":"2025-12-06T07:41:21","date_gmt":"2025-12-06T04:41:21","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/emuseum.torus.kz\/exhibit\/68db59d5989fa237a-en\/"},"modified":"2025-12-31T12:55:12","modified_gmt":"2025-12-31T09:55:12","slug":"68db59d5989fa237a-en","status":"publish","type":"exhibit","link":"https:\/\/e-museum.kz\/en\/exhibit\/68db59d5989fa237a-en\/","title":{"rendered":"Tombstone."},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Tombstone. This white marble tombstone was erected in 1881 by Lieutenant General G.A.Kolpakovsky on the grave of Chokan Valikhanov under the direction of the Turkestan Governor-General K.P.von Kaufman.<br \/>\nAn inscription is engraved on the surface of the monument:<br \/>\n\u201cHERE LIES THE REMAINS OF STAFF RITTMEISTER CHOKAN CHINGISOVICH VALIKHANOV, DECEASED IN 1865.\u201d<br \/>\nBelow the inscription are two crescent moons facing in opposite directions, separated by an arrow. Beneath that is another inscription:<br \/>\n\u201cAt the request of the Turkestan Governor-General, Adjutant General von Kaufman, in recognition of Valikhanov\u2019s scientific contributions, this monument was erected by Lieutenant General Kolpakovsky in 1881.\u201d<br \/>\nThe monument was deliberately split in the middle\u2014traces of the crack are still visible at the center.19th century.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":0,"menu_order":0,"template":"","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"","ast-site-content-layout":"default","site-content-style":"default","site-sidebar-style":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"","footer-sml-layout":"","ast-disable-related-posts":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","header-above-stick-meta":"","header-main-stick-meta